            <h2>From <span class="text-primary">Physical Space</span> to <span class="text-primary">Digital Space</span></h2>
            <p>Understanding the human-centered approach through physical space and functionality can be directly applied to the science of user-experience and the web-based spaces we interact with daily. 
                
                From <span class="text-primary">spacial architecture</span> to <span class="text-primary">information architecture </span>. 
                
                From <span class="text-primary">Way-finding </span>to <span class="text-primary">wire-framing</span>.</p>
                
                Over my 17 years as an architectural and interior designer, I have gained the knowledge and experience of user-centric design thought ideation. I have mastered expertise in approaching each project and design problem with the end-user in mind, through direct interviews, community input, and research. All of the built environments I have designed and worked through into completion have given me the insight and experience to understand how to implement my client's needs in the most thoughtful, cost-effective ways through interdisiplinary design and creative problem-solving skills.
